12 (b) (1) Subject to § 2–103.4 of this article, the Administration may establish a
13 personnel system based on merit and fitness.
14 (2) The Administration may:
15 (i) Subject to Division II of the State Personnel and Pensions
16 Article, participate in the Employees’ Retirement System and the Employees’ Pension
17 System of the State of Maryland on terms and conditions mutually acceptable to the
18 Administration and the Board of Trustees for the State Retirement and Pension System;
19 and
20 (ii) Establish and maintain an independent system of pensions and
21 retirement benefits for its employees.
22 (c) The Administrator may appoint and remove all employees of the
23 Administration, subject to the rules of procedure and standards that the Secretary adopts.
24 (D) (1) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, THE
25 MARYLAND TRANSPORTATION COMMISSION SHALL DETERMINE THE
26 QUALIFICATIONS AND APPOINTMENTS, AS WELL AS COMPENSATION AND LEAVE,
27 FOR UP TO 12 MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL POSITIONS REQUIRED BY THE
28 ADMINISTRATION TO OPERATE AND ADMINISTER ALL STATE–OWNED TRANSIT
29 FACILITIES.
30 (2) (I) IN MAKING DETERMINATIONS AND APPOINTMENTS UNDER
