1 (a) Subject to the provisions of this section, the Administration is liable for its
2 contracts and torts and for the torts of its officers, agents, and employees in connection with
3 the performance of the duties and functions of the Administration under this title.
4 (b) (1) The exclusive remedy for a breach of contract or for a tort committed by
5 the Administration, its officers, agents, or employees is a suit against the Administration.
6 (2) No execution may be levied on any property of this State or of the
7 Administration.
8 (c) THE LIABILITY OF THE ADMINISTRATION AS TO A TORT ACTION MAY
9 NOT EXCEED $400,000 TO A SINGLE CLAIMANT FOR INJURIES ARISING FROM A
10 SINGLE INCIDENT OR OCCURRENCE.
11 (D) Subsection [(d)] (E) of this section does not apply to a tort claim that is
12 asserted by cross–claim, counterclaim, or third–party claim.
13 [(d)] (E) A tort claimant may not institute an action under this section unless:
14 (1) The claimant submits a written notice of claim to the Administrator or
15 the Administrator’s designee within 1 year after the injury to person or property that is the
16 basis of the claim;
17 (2) The Administrator or the Administrator’s designee denies the claim;
18 and
19 (3) The action is filed within 3 years after the cause of action arises.
20 [(e)] (F) A notice of claim under this section shall:
21 (1) Contain a concise statement of facts that sets forth the nature of the
22 claim, including the date and place of the alleged tort;
23 (2) State the name and address of the claimant;
24 (3) State the name, address, and telephone number of counsel for the
25 claimant, if any; and
26 (4) Be signed by the claimant, or the legal representative or counsel for the
27 claimant.
28 [(f)] (G) A claim under this section is denied:

