10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, (Three–fifths of all the members
11 elected to each of the two Houses concurring), That it be proposed that the Maryland
12 Constitution read as follows:
13 Article III – Legislative Department
14 40B.
15 The General Assembly shall enact no law authorizing private property to be taken
16 for public use without just compensation, to be agreed upon between the parties or awarded
17 by a jury, being first paid or tendered to the party entitled to such compensation, except
18 that where such property in the judgment of the State [Roads Commission] HIGHWAY
19 ADMINISTRATION, OR A SUCCESSOR STATE AGENCY, is needed by the State for
20 highway purposes OR OF THE MARYLAND TRANSIT ADMINISTRATION, OR A
21 SUCCESSOR STATE AGENCY, IS NEEDED BY THE STATE FOR TRANSIT PURPOSES, the
22 General Assembly may provide that such property may be taken immediately upon
23 payment therefor to the owner or owners thereof by said State [Roads Commission]
24 HIGHWAY ADMINISTRATION OR MARYLAND TRANSIT ADMINISTRATION, OR ANY
25 RESPECTIVE SUCCESSOR STATE AGENCIES, or into Court, such amount as said State
26 [Roads Commission] HIGHWAY ADMINISTRATION OR MARYLAND TRANSIT
27 ADMINISTRATION, OR ANY RESPECTIVE STATE AGENCIES, shall estimate to be of the
28 fair value of said property, provided such legislation also requires the payment of any
29 further sum that may subsequently be awarded by a jury.
30 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
31 as follows:
32 Article – Transportation
33 7–401.1.
34 (A) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPHS (2) AND (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION, IF
35 PROPERTY IS TO BE CONDEMNED FOR A TRANSIT PURPOSE, THE ADMINISTRATION
36 SHALL CONDEMN THE NECESSARY PROPERTY UNDER THIS SECTION.

SENATE BILL 947 17
1 (2) IF THE ADMINISTRATION CONSIDERS THE PROCEDURES UNDER
2 THIS SECTION INAPPROPRIATE, THE PROPERTY MAY BE CONDEMNED BY THE
3 ADMINISTRATION UNDER § 7–401.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE OR TITLE 12 OF THE REAL
4 PROPERTY ARTICLE.
5 (3) EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE PROVIDED IN THIS SECTION,
6 CONDEMNATION PROCEEDINGS UNDER THIS SECTION SHALL FOLLOW THE
7 PROCEDURES SET FORTH IN TITLE 12 OF THE REAL PROPERTY ARTICLE AND THE
8 MARYLAND RULES.
9 (B) (1) BEFORE ANY PROPERTY IS CONDEMNED UNDER THIS SECTION
10 THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL:
11 (I) COMPLETE APPROPRIATE ENGINEERING AND OTHER
12 STUDIES; AND
13 (II) PREPARE A CONSTRUCTION PLAN THAT SHOWS THE
14 LOCATION OF THE TRANSIT FACILITY TO BE CONSTRUCTED, IMPROVED, OR
15 RECONSTRUCTED.
16 (2) AFTER PREPARING THE CONSTRUCTION PLAN, THE
17 ADMINISTRATION SHALL PREPARE PLATS THAT INCLUDE:
18 (I) THE CONSTRUCTION PLAN;
19 (II) THE FEE SIMPLE AND EASEMENT AREA TO BE ACQUIRED;
20 AND
21 (III) THE PROPERTY LINES OF THE PROPERTY OWNERS WHOSE
22 PROPERTY WILL BE AFFECTED BY THE ACQUISITION.
23 (3) AFTER THE PLATS ARE PREPARED, THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL:
24 (I) MAKE THE ENGINEERING AND REAL ESTATE STUDIES,
25 EVALUATIONS, AND INVESTIGATIONS NECESSARY TO DETERMINE, IN ITS OPINION:
26 1. THE FAIR VALUE OF THE PROPERTY TO BE ACQUIRED;
27 AND
28 2. THE FAIR COMPENSATION FOR ANY RESULTING
29 DAMAGES TO THE REMAINING PROPERTY OF THE OWNER;

18 SENATE BILL 947
1 (II) PREPARE AN ESTIMATE OF THIS FAIR VALUE AND FAIR
2 COMPENSATION; AND
3 (III) PROVIDE FOR PAYMENT OF THESE ESTIMATED AMOUNTS AS
4 REQUIRED BY SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION.
5 (C) (1) THE PLATS PREPARED BY THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL BE FILED
6 FOR RECORD WITH THE STATE ARCHIVES.
7 (2) PLATS FILED WITH THE STATE ARCHIVES SHALL BE
8 ELECTRONICALLY RECORDED AS PROVIDED IN § 9–1011 OF THE STATE
9 GOVERNMENT ARTICLE.
10 (D) (1) THE PLATS AND ESTIMATES APPROVED BY THE ADMINISTRATION
11 SHALL BE KEPT AS PART OF THE PERMANENT RECORDS OF THE ADMINISTRATION.
12 (2) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER STATUTE TO THE CONTRARY:
13 (I) EXCEPT AS ALLOWED BY THE ADMINISTRATION, THE PLATS
14 PREPARED BY THE ADMINISTRATION ARE NOT PUBLIC INFORMATION OR OPEN TO
15 PUBLIC INSPECTION UNTIL THEY HAVE BEEN RECORDED; AND
16 (II) EXCEPT WHEN FILED WITH A BOARD OF PROPERTY REVIEW
17 ESTABLISHED UNDER § 8–327 OF THIS ARTICLE OR A COURT, THE ESTIMATES
18 PREPARED BY THE ADMINISTRATION ARE NOT PUBLIC INFORMATION OR OPEN TO
19 PUBLIC INSPECTION UNTIL ALL THE PROPERTY SHOWN ON THE PLATS HAS BEEN
20 ACQUIRED OR ITS PRICE DETERMINED.
21 (E) (1) AFTER THE PLATS ARE FILED FOR RECORD, THE
22 ADMINISTRATION IMMEDIATELY SHALL:
23 (I) FILE, IN THE COURT FOR THE COUNTY IN WHICH THE
24 PROPERTY TO BE ACQUIRED IS LOCATED, A PETITION FOR CONDEMNATION THAT
25 INCLUDES:
26 1. THE NAME AND ADDRESS OF THE PROPERTY OWNER;
27 2. THE LOCATION OF THE PROPERTY TO BE ACQUIRED;
28 AND
29 3. THE ESTIMATED FAIR VALUE OF THE PROPERTY TO
30 BE ACQUIRED AND ESTIMATED FAIR COMPENSATION FOR ANY DAMAGE RESULTING
31 TO THE REMAINING PROPERTY OF THE OWNER; AND

SENATE BILL 947 19
1 (II) PAY TO THE OWNER OF THE PROPERTY OR INTO THE COURT
2 FOR THE OWNER’S BENEFIT, THE ESTIMATED FAIR VALUE AND FAIR COMPENSATION
3 SPECIFIED IN THE PETITION.
4 (2) ON WRITTEN REQUEST TO THE CLERK OF THE COURT, THE
5 PROPERTY OWNER IS ENTITLED TO RECEIVE ANY AMOUNT PAID INTO THE COURT
6 FOR THE PROPERTY OWNER’S BENEFIT, WITHIN 10 BUSINESS DAYS OF THE
7 REQUEST, WITHOUT PREJUDICE TO ANY OF THE PROPERTY OWNER’S RIGHTS, IF THE
8 PROPERTY OWNER AGREES TO REPAY TO THE ADMINISTRATION ANY EXCESS OF
9 THAT AMOUNT OVER THE FINAL AWARD THAT IS ALLOWED IN THE SUBSEQUENT
10 CONDEMNATION PROCEEDINGS.
11 (3) A PAYMENT MADE UNDER THIS SECTION DOES NOT LIMIT IN ANY
12 WAY THE AMOUNT OF THE FINAL AWARD THAT MAY BE ALLOWED IN THE
13 SUBSEQUENT CONDEMNATION PROCEEDINGS.
14 (F) (1) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION,
15 AFTER THE PETITION IS FILED AND PAYMENT IS MADE UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF
16 THIS SECTION:
17 (I) THE ADMINISTRATION MAY TAKE POSSESSION OF THE
18 PROPERTY TO BE ACQUIRED, AS SHOWN ON THE RECORDED PLATS;
19 (II) THE ADMINISTRATION MAY PROCEED WITH
20 CONSTRUCTION WITHOUT INTERFERENCE BY THE OWNER; AND
21 (III) WITH THE PERMISSION OF THE ADMINISTRATION AND
22 UNDER ITS SUPERVISION, ANY PUBLIC OR PRIVATE UTILITY MAY INSTALL ITS
23 FACILITIES ON ANY LAND BEING ACQUIRED BY THE ADMINISTRATION IN FEE
24 SIMPLE.
25 (2) UNLESS THE OWNER AGREES OTHERWISE, IF A DWELLING OR
26 PLACE OF BUSINESS IS TAKEN, THE RESIDENT OR OCCUPANT NEED NOT VACATE THE
27 DWELLING OR PLACE OF BUSINESS UNTIL THE TITLE TO THE PROPERTY HAS BEEN
28 ACQUIRED BY DEED OR CONDEMNATION.
29 (G) (1) AFTER THE PETITION IS FILED AND PAYMENT IS MADE UNDER
30 SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION, THE ADMINISTRATION SHALL SEEK TO ACQUIRE
31 THE PROPERTY BY AMICABLE NEGOTIATION.
32 (2) FOR PURPOSES OF THESE NEGOTIATIONS, THE ADMINISTRATION
33 SHALL DETERMINE THE VALUE OF THE PROPERTY TO BE ACQUIRED AS OF THE DATE

20 SENATE BILL 947
1 THE PAYMENT IS MADE TO THE PROPERTY OWNER OR INTO COURT UNDER
2 SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION.
3 (H) (1) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, IF
4 THE ADMINISTRATION IS UNABLE TO ACQUIRE THE PROPERTY BY NEGOTIATION, IT
5 SHALL CERTIFY THE CASE TO THE BOARD OF PROPERTY REVIEW FOR THE COUNTY
6 IN WHICH THE PROPERTY IS LOCATED, AS PROVIDED IN THE MARYLAND RULES.
7 (2) A CASE SHALL BE FILED AS A CONDEMNATION CASE IN THE COURT
8 FOR THE COUNTY IN WHICH THE PROPERTY IS LOCATED AND MAY NOT BE HEARD BY
9 A BOARD OF PROPERTY REVIEW IF:
10 (I) THE ADMINISTRATION DETERMINES THAT VALID,
11 MARKETABLE TITLE IS UNOBTAINABLE WITHOUT A COURT PROCEEDING; OR
12 (II) A NONRESIDENT HAS AN INTEREST IN THE PROPERTY AND
13 WILL NOT ACCEPT SERVICE OF PROCESS AND AGREE TO THE BOARD’S
14 JURISDICTION.
15 (I) IF, WITHIN 1 YEAR AFTER PAYMENT IS MADE UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF
16 THIS SECTION, THE ADMINISTRATION FAILS TO ASCERTAIN THE ENTIRE AMOUNT TO
17 BE PAID FOR THE PROPERTY AND ACQUIRE TITLE TO IT BY DEED OR CONDEMNATION
18 OR, WITHIN THAT SAME 1–YEAR PERIOD, FAILS TO FILE TIMELY A PETITION FOR
19 CONDEMNATION AS REQUIRED BY THE MARYLAND RULES, THEN THE FAIR VALUE
20 OF THE PROPERTY SHALL BE THE GREATER OF THE VALUES DETERMINED AS OF:
21 (1) THE DATE THE TITLE TO THE PROPERTY IS ACQUIRED; AND
22 (2) THE DATE THE PAYMENT WAS MADE UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF
23 THIS SECTION.
24 (J) AT THE CONCLUSION OF ALL PROCEEDINGS, THE ADMINISTRATION
25 SHALL PAY TO THE PROPERTY OWNER:
26 (1) ANY EXCESS OF THE FINAL AWARD OVER THE AMOUNT PAID
27 UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION; AND
28 (2) INTEREST ON THE EXCESS FROM THE DATE OF PAYMENT UNDER
29 SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION AT THE RATE OF 6% A YEAR.
